DESCRIPTION
scripts/dogfood-capture.sh hand-rolls 4 sequential 'etude capture' calls per bead. etude-jb7 shipped 'etude capture-run <spec.yaml>' for batch multi-stage capture in one operation. Rewrite dogfood-capture.sh to emit a capture-run YAML spec (plan/implement/verify/review stages) and invoke capture-run once, reducing the 4-call sequence to a single batch op. Verify the captured run manifest is equivalent.

DESIGN
## Plan

**Approach:** Rewrite `scripts/dogfood-capture.sh` to emit ONE `capture-run`
YAML spec describing all four dev-workflow stages and invoke `etude capture-run`
once, replacing the 4 sequential `etude capture` append calls. Field-by-field
the two paths build the SAME `runmanifest.Stage` struct, so the resulting
manifest is equivalent (proven below). Same arg interface, same fresh build,
same push, same summary. Path-confinement (etude-094) forces all five artifacts
to be staged INTO the spec dir and referenced by relative basename.

**Key fidelity finding — capture-run DOES inherit run-level -> stage.**
`internal/cli/capture_run.go` buildStage() inherits run-level `git_sha`
(L283-288), `harness`/`harness_version` (L305-313), and `model` (L315-319) to
any stage that omits them; `skill.repo`/`skill.version` default to
"manual"/"manual" (L291-298) matching the old script (which only set
--skill-id). `produced_by` defaults to "original" (L277-280). Confirmed by
`TestCaptureRunHappyPath3Stages` (stage 0 uses run-level model) and
`TestCaptureRunRunLevelGitSHAAppliedToAllStages`. So: put shared
harness/harness_version/git_sha at RUN level; set model PER STAGE (it varies:
opus for plan/verify/review, sonnet for implement); set produced_by:original
per stage (explicit, matches old --produced-by original); refs {bead:<bead>} at
run level.

**Equivalence proof (struct-level).** Old `capture` (capture.go:195-211) and
new `capture-run` (capture_run.go:351-367) construct the identical
`runmanifest.Stage{Name, ProducedBy, GitSHA, Skill{ID,Repo,Version},
Producer{Harness{Name,Version}, Model, Skill}, Inputs, Output, Timestamp}`.
Both read artifacts via inferMediaType + store.AddContent, so role +
content-hash + media-type are byte-identical for the same file content.
Run-level Workflow/WorkflowVersion: old script passes `--workflow default
--workflow-version v1`; spec sets the same -> identical (NOT the capture-run
"manual"/"manual-v1" defaults, because we set them explicitly).

**Spec shape — `$specdir/run.yaml`** (heredoc; <bead>/<ver>/<commit> interpolated):
```yaml
run_id: <bead>
workflow: default
workflow_version: v1
git_sha: <full-40-hex-commit>
harness: claude-code
harness_version: <claude --version, or unknown>
refs:
  bead: <bead>
stages:
  - stage: plan
    produced_by: original
    model: claude-opus-4-7
    skill: {id: dev-planner}
    inputs:  [{role: task, path: task.md}]
    output:   {role: plan, path: plan.md}
  - stage: implement
    produced_by: original
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    skill: {id: dev-coder}
    inputs:  [{role: plan, path: plan.md}]
    output:   {role: diff, path: diff.patch}
  - stage: verify
    produced_by: original
    model: claude-opus-4-7
    skill: {id: dev-qa}
    inputs:  [{role: diff, path: diff.patch}]
    output:   {role: verify, path: verify.md}
  - stage: review
    produced_by: original
    model: claude-opus-4-7
    skill: {id: dev-pr-reviewer}
    inputs:  [{role: diff, path: diff.patch}, {role: verify, path: verify.md}]
    output:   {role: review, path: review.md}
```
(Stage `model` is per-stage because it varies; the rest inherit run-level. Could
instead set model: claude-opus-4-7 at run level + a single sonnet override on
implement — equivalent; per-stage is clearer.)

**Artifact staging (relative-path mechanics).** capture-run REJECTS absolute
paths and confines realpath to the spec dir. The old script used absolute
`$tmp/...` AND the verify/review args are absolute (/tmp). So:
- create a dedicated `specdir="$(mktemp -d)"` (add to the EXIT trap rm -rf).
- write the 3 GENERATED artifacts directly into specdir by relative name:
  `bd show <bead>` -> `$specdir/task.md`; bead design (python json extractor)
  -> `$specdir/plan.md`; `git show <commit>` -> `$specdir/diff.patch`.
- COPY the 2 ARG files in: `cp -- "$verify_file" "$specdir/verify.md"` and
  `cp -- "$review_file" "$specdir/review.md"`. (Renaming to fixed basenames
  keeps the spec stable regardless of the source filenames; content is what
  the hash captures, so renaming is immaterial to equivalence.)
- write `$specdir/run.yaml` referencing every artifact by BARE basename
  (task.md, plan.md, diff.patch, verify.md, review.md). diff.patch feeds both
  implement(output) and verify+review(input); plan.md feeds plan(output) and
  implement(input) — same relative path each time, so capture-run de-dupes to
  one content-addressed blob (artifactStore keys by hash), exactly as the old
  4-call path did.
- keep `bin="$bindir/etude"` fresh-build unchanged; invoke
  `"$bin" capture-run "$specdir/run.yaml"`.

**Create-only decision.** capture-run is create-only: it ERRORS with "run ...
already exists" if `refs/etude/runs/<bead>` exists (capture_run.go:240-249;
TestCaptureRunCreateOnlyCollision). The old 4-call path APPENDED, so a re-run
silently produced a duplicated/8-stage manifest. Erroring on re-run is STRICTLY
BETTER for a one-shot dogfood capture (no accidental double-capture); accept and
document it in the header. If a legitimate re-capture is ever needed, delete the
ref first (`git update-ref -d refs/etude/runs/<bead>` + delete on origin) — note
this in the header comment, do not auto-delete.

**Behavior preserved.** set -euo pipefail; arg interface `<bead> <commit>
<verify-file> <review-file>`; `git rev-parse --verify <commit>^{commit}` ->
full 40-hex; pre-check both arg files exist; fresh `go build -o $bin
./cmd/etude`; EXIT trap cleans bindir+tmp/specdir; `git push origin
refs/etude/runs/<bead>`; final `"$bin" run show <bead> | grep -E
"stage:|model:|skill:"` summary.

