**Tests:** This is a bash script (no Go unit test). Verify is a scripted
equivalence check against a REAL recently-closed bead (etude-094), run in a
THROWAWAY ref namespace so it never touches real refs/etude/runs/*:

  # 0. pick a real closed bead + its commit, and have its verify/review md files
  B=etude-094; C=$(git rev-parse --verify "<commit-of-094>^{commit}")
  VF=/tmp/094-verify.md; RF=/tmp/094-review.md   # real artifacts
  # 1. build etude fresh once
  go build -o /tmp/etude-eq ./cmd/etude
  # 2. OLD path -> ref refs/etude/runs/eq-old (4 capture calls, mirror old flags)
  #    NEW path -> ref refs/etude/runs/eq-new (single capture-run on a spec dir)
  #    For both, use run_id eq-old / eq-new so they live in throwaway refs.
  # 3. extract both manifests and normalise timestamps, then diff:
  for r in eq-old eq-new; do
    /tmp/etude-eq run show "$r" --json 2>/dev/null \
      | python3 -c 'import sys,json,re; d=json.load(sys.stdin); \
        d.pop("created",None); d["run_id"]="RUN"; \
        [s.update({"timestamp":"TS"}) for s in d.get("stages",[])]; \
        print(json.dumps(d,sort_keys=True,indent=2))' > /tmp/$r.json
  done
  diff /tmp/eq-old.json /tmp/eq-new.json   # EXPECT: empty (modulo run_id/timestamps)
  # 4. cleanup throwaway refs
  git update-ref -d refs/etude/runs/eq-old; git update-ref -d refs/etude/runs/eq-new

Acceptance: the diff is empty after normalising run_id + all timestamps. Stage
names+order, per-stage skill{id,repo=manual,version=manual}, model, produced_by,
git_sha, harness/harness_version, every input (role+content-hash+media_type) and
output, and run-level workflow/workflow_version/refs must match. Also run the
built script end-to-end on a throwaway run_id (manual CLI test per dev-workflow)
and confirm `run show` summary + push succeed. NOTE: the real run-id collision
means the equivalence harness MUST use eq-old/eq-new, not the real bead id; the
`--run`/run_id is the only intentional difference and is normalised out.

