## PLAN-GATE CORRECTION (3-seat: ALL THREE BLOCK'd — core design unanimously sound, VERIFICATION + one fidelity bug need fixing)
The struct-equivalence/inheritance/path-staging/create-only/scope decisions are all confirmed correct by every seat. Three concrete defects to fix (all verified against source):

**FIX 1 (Opus + codex) — the equivalence Verify uses a non-existent flag.** `etude run show` has NO `--json` flag (run.go:60-71: ExactArgs(1), zero flags; dogfood-gate-capture.sh:59 notes this). The Verify must instead diff the RAW manifest blobs: `git cat-file -p refs/etude/runs/<ref>:manifest.json` for each, normalize, then `diff`.

**FIX 2 (codex) — media_type fidelity when staging the arg files.** The old `capture` infers media_type from the ORIGINAL arg path via inferMediaType (capture.go:588, extension-based: .txt→text/plain, .md/.markdown→text/markdown, default text/plain). Renaming the verify_file/review_file args to a fixed `verify.md`/`review.md` changes the inferred media_type for any non-.md arg (extensionless, .txt, …), making ArtifactRef.MediaType diverge even when content hashes match. FIX: when staging the two arg files, PRESERVE their source extension — `vext="${verify_file##*.}"` (guard the no-dot case: if "$vext" == "$verify_file" then no extension → stage with no extension) and stage as `verify.$vext` / `review.$rext`; reference that basename in the spec. The three GENERATED artifacts keep their fixed names (task.md/plan.md/diff.patch) — identical to the old script's $tmp/task.md, $tmp/plan.md, $tmp/diff.patch, so their media_type is already faithful.

**FIX 3 (gemini) — the equivalence normalization misses refs.bead.** If the test captures into throwaway run-ids eq-old/eq-new with `--ref bead=eq-old` / `refs:{bead: eq-new}`, the manifests' `refs.bead` differ and the strict diff falsely fails. FIX: normalize ALL volatile fields before diffing — `run_id`, `created`, every stage `timestamp`, AND `refs.bead` (set each to a constant). (Alternatively decouple run-id from the bead ref so refs.bead matches; but normalizing all four is simplest/most robust.)

## CORRECTED VERIFICATION (the Verify-phase equivalence proof)
In a throwaway clone/worktree (do NOT pollute real refs), capture a real closed bead's artifacts BOTH ways into two run-ids (eq-old via the OLD 4-capture sequence; eq-new via the NEW capture-run script), each with the same artifact contents. Then:
```
for r in eq-old eq-new; do
  git cat-file -p "refs/etude/runs/$r:manifest.json" | python3 -c '
import sys,json
m=json.load(sys.stdin)
m["run_id"]="X"; m["created"]="T"
if "refs" in m and "bead" in m["refs"]: m["refs"]["bead"]="X"
for s in m.get("stages",[]): s["timestamp"]="T"
json.dump(m,sys.stdout,indent=2,sort_keys=True)' > "/tmp/eq-$r.json"
done
diff /tmp/eq-eq-old.json /tmp/eq-eq-new.json && echo EQUIVALENT
```
Expect empty diff (EQUIVALENT). This compares stage order, per-stage skill{id,repo,version}/model/produced_by/git_sha/harness/harness_version, inputs (role+artifact hash+media_type), output (role+artifact hash+media_type), and run-level workflow/workflow_version — exactly the fidelity surface, including the artifact hashes + media_types that `run show` text would omit.

All other plan decisions stand unchanged.


